parameters.description: Log of COTS intrinsic growth rate (year^-1). Transformed value is approximately 0.5, representing 50% annual population growth under ideal conditions.
Log of COTS carrying capacity (individuals/m2). Transformed value is approximately 2.0, representing maximum sustainable COTS density.
Log of COTS predation rate on slow-growing corals (m2/individual/year). Transformed value is approximately 0.1, representing area of slow-growing coral consumed per COTS per year.
Log of COTS predation rate on fast-growing corals (m2/individual/year). Transformed value is approximately 0.2, representing area of fast-growing coral consumed per COTS per year.
Log of COTS preference for fast-growing corals (dimensionless). Transformed value is approximately 2.0, indicating COTS prefer fast-growing corals twice as much as slow-growing ones.
Log of slow-growing coral intrinsic growth rate (year^-1). Transformed value is approximately 0.1, representing 10% annual growth under ideal conditions.
Log of fast-growing coral intrinsic growth rate (year^-1). Transformed value is approximately 0.5, representing 50% annual growth under ideal conditions.
Log of slow-growing coral carrying capacity (%). Transformed value is approximately 50%, representing maximum possible cover for slow-growing corals.
Log of fast-growing coral carrying capacity (%). Transformed value is approximately 30%, representing maximum possible cover for fast-growing corals.
Log of optimal temperature for COTS (°C). Transformed value is approximately 28°C, representing the temperature at which COTS have highest growth/survival.
Log of temperature tolerance width for COTS (°C). Transformed value is approximately 2°C, representing the width of the temperature response curve.
Log of temperature threshold for coral stress (°C). Transformed value is approximately 30°C, above which corals experience increased mortality.
Log of slope of temperature effect on coral mortality (dimensionless). Transformed value is approximately 0.5, controlling how quickly mortality increases with temperature.
Log of minimum coral cover needed for COTS survival (%). Transformed value is approximately 5%, representing the coral cover below which COTS population growth is severely limited.
Log of standard deviation for COTS observations. Transformed value is approximately 0.2, representing observation error.
Log of standard deviation for slow-growing coral observations. Transformed value is approximately 0.3, representing observation error.
Log of standard deviation for fast-growing coral observations. Transformed value is approximately 0.3, representing observation error.
